data.chText: 陆标，地标（有助于识别所处地点的大建筑物等）
data.enText: something, such as a large building, that you can see clearly from a distance and that will help you to know where you are

data.chText: 帝国大厦是人们熟悉的纽约高楼大厦中的地标。
data.enText: The Empire State Building is a familiar landmark on the New York skyline.
an event, a discovery, an invention, etc. that marks an important stage in sth

data.chText: 停火协定被看作是与恐怖主义斗争的重要里程碑。
data.enText: The ceasefire was seen as a major landmark in the fight against terrorism.

data.chText: 具有里程碑意义的决策 / 法庭裁决
data.enText: a landmark decision/ruling in the courts

data.chText: 有历史意义的建筑物（或遗址）
data.enText: a building or a place that is very important because of its history, and that should be preserved

simple_means.memory_skill: land 地 + mark 记号，符号 → 地上的标志 → 里程碑

means: 陆标(有助于识别所处地点的大建筑物等)
有历史意义的建筑物(或遗址)

tr: an anatomical structure used as a point of origin in locating other anatomical structures (as in surgery) or as point from which measurements can be taken
a mark showing the boundary of a piece of land
an event marking a unique or important historical change of course or one on which important developments depend
example: the agreement was a watershed in the history of both nations

tr: the position of a prominent or well-known object in a particular landscape
example: the church steeple provided a convenient landmark

value.def: A landmark is a building or feature which is easily noticed and can be used to judge your position or the position of other buildings or features.

example.ex: The Ambassador Hotel is a Los Angeles landmark.
example.tran: 国宾大饭店是洛杉矶的地标性建筑之一。

value.def: You can refer to an important stage in the development of something as a landmark .

example.tran: 里程碑式的军备控制条约

example.ex: The baby was one of the big landmarks in our relationship.
example.tran: 孩子的出世是我们俩关系中的一个重要转折点。

trans: 置地广场；置地廣場；中环置地广场

partsOfSpeech.dec: book 书 + mark 记号，符号 → 书签
de 加强 + marc〔= mark〕记号，符号 + ate 做，造成，使… → 加强标志 → 划分界线
hall 大 + mark 记号，符号 → 大记号 → 标志
land 地 + mark 记号，符号 → 地上的标志 → 里程碑
marks 记号，指靶中心的符号 + man 人 → 打枪中靶的人 → 神枪手
post 邮政 + mark 记号，符号 → 邮戳
re 一再 + mark 记号，符号 → 一再做记号 → 评论，意见
re 一再 + mark 记号，符号 + able …的 → 一再做标记的 → 不平常的；值得注意的
tide 潮 + mark 记号，符号 → （沙滩等处潮水留下的）潮痕
trade 贸易 + mark 记号，符号 → 商标
un 不，无，没有 + mark 记号，符号 + ed 表形容词 → 无记号的
